detect.prompt:
TASK: Detect objects in this image that match the specified labels.

Description: ${description}
Labels to detect: ${labels}
Minimum confidence: ${confidence_threshold}

For each detected object, provide:
1. The label (must be from the provided labels list)
2. Bounding box with normalized coordinates (0-1 range)
3. Confidence score (0-1)

Coordinate system:
- x,y is the top-left corner of the box
- x increases left to right (0 = left edge, 1 = right edge)
- y increases top to bottom (0 = top edge, 1 = bottom edge)
- width and height are also normalized (0-1)

Return JSON:
{
    "detections": [
        {
            "label": "object_name",
            "bbox": {"x": 0.1, "y": 0.2, "width": 0.3, "height": 0.4},
            "confidence": 0.95
        }
    ]
}

Only include objects you can clearly identify with confidence >= ${confidence_threshold}.

